net.bytebuddy.instrumentation

Class Instrumentation.Context.Default

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.bytebuddy.instrumentation.Instrumentation.Context.Default
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Instrumentation.Context, Instrumentation.Context.ExtractableView, AuxiliaryType.MethodAccessorFactory
    Enclosing interface:
    Instrumentation.Context

    public static class Instrumentation.Context.Default
extends Object
implements Instrumentation.Context.ExtractableView, AuxiliaryType.MethodAccessorFactory
    A default implementation of an Instrumentation.Context.ExtractableView which serves as its own AuxiliaryType.MethodAccessorFactory.

        public MethodDescription registerGetterFor(FieldDescription fieldDescription)
        Description copied from interface: AuxiliaryType.MethodAccessorFactory
        Registers a getter for the given FieldDescription which might itself not be accessible from outside the class. The returned getter method defines the field type as its return type, does not take any arguments and is of package-private visibility, similarly to the Java compiler's accessor methods. If the field is static, this accessor method is also static.
        Specified by:
        registerGetterFor in interface AuxiliaryType.MethodAccessorFactory
        Parameters:

        Returns:

The returned setter method defines the field type as its only argument type, returns void and is of package-private visibility, similarly to the Java compiler's accessor methods.       • cache

        public FieldDescription cache(StackManipulation fieldValue,
                              TypeDescription fieldType)
        Description copied from interface: Instrumentation.Context
        Caches a single value by storing it in form of a private, final and static field. By caching values, expensive instance creations can be avoided and object identity can be preserved. The field is initiated in a generated class's static initializer.
        Specified by:
        cache in interface Instrumentation.Context
        Parameters:
        fieldValue - A stack manipulation for creating the value that is to be cached in a static field. After executing the stack manipulation, exactly one value must be put onto the operand stack which is assignable to the given fieldType.
        fieldType - The type of the field for storing the cached value. This field's type determines the value that is put onto the operand stack by this method's returned stack manipulation.
        Returns:
        A description of a field that was defined on the instrumented type which contains the given value.

                  TypeWriter.MethodPool methodPool,
                  Instrumentation.Context.ExtractableView.InjectedCode injectedCode)
        Description copied from interface: Instrumentation.Context.ExtractableView
        Writes any information that was registered with an Instrumentation.Context to the provided class visitor. This contains any fields for value caching, any accessor method and it writes the type initializer. The type initializer must therefore never be written manually.
